Dozens of Ukrainian troops are reported to have been killed at a military base in Mykolaiv in southern Ukraine following Russian strikes on Friday March 18. (Niclas Hammarstrom/Expressen)
        
 

Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveRussian forces have fired two missiles at a Ukrainian military unit on the outskirts of Dnipro, the fourth-largest city in the country, according to regional emergency services.
The attacks destroyed buildings and set off two fires, it said, while the number of those killed and wounded was still being established.
Dnipro is west of the regions along the Russian border that have been controlled by Russian-backed separatists since 2014.
